  m_Name: Lesson_PlayerInitiatedMovement_3
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  ClassroomTitle: Player Initiated Movement (Strafing Enabled)
  LessonSteps:
  - m_DialogueString: "Welcome back to the classroom. You have just experienced the
      third variant of Player Initiated Movement. \r"
    m_ClearPreviousImage: 1
    m_MainImage: {fileID: 0}
    m_VoiceoverClip: {fileID: 0}
  - m_DialogueString: "Take a moment and think about how this experience differs
      with your previous experience. Did the controls feel more intuitive? Were you
      more comfortable?\r"
    m_ClearPreviousImage: 1
    m_MainImage: {fileID: 0}
    m_VoiceoverClip: {fileID: 0}
  - m_DialogueString: 'In this third design implementation, controls have been enabled
      to allow lateral movement, also known as strafing, using the joystick. '
    m_ClearPreviousImage: 1
    m_MainImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: b8faf5119957ef14ca6b5831f4fcec2d, type: 3}
    m_VoiceoverClip: {fileID: 0}
  - m_DialogueString: "This dual-axis movement is a combination of strafing and surging.
      It might be tempting to give players more control over their movements. However,
      it is a double edged sword.\r"
    m_ClearPreviousImage: 1
    m_MainImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: b8faf5119957ef14ca6b5831f4fcec2d, type: 3}
    m_VoiceoverClip: {fileID: 0}
  - m_DialogueString: "Similar to acceleration, strafing in Virtual Reality causes
      vection due to a mismatch between perceived motion and actual physical motion.
      \r"
    m_ClearPreviousImage: 1
    m_MainImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 762a6196fad3d6d458bd5d806c203d8a, type: 3}
    m_VoiceoverClip: {fileID: 0}
  - m_DialogueString: "This results in a visual-proprioception mismatch. \r"
    m_ClearPreviousImage: 1
    m_MainImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 762a6196fad3d6d458bd5d806c203d8a, type: 3}
    m_VoiceoverClip: {fileID: 0}
  - m_DialogueString: "Proprioception refers to the perception or awareness of the
      position, movement, and extent of the body and its constituent parts.\r"
    m_ClearPreviousImage: 1
    m_MainImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 762a6196fad3d6d458bd5d806c203d8a, type: 3}
    m_VoiceoverClip: {fileID: 0}
  - m_DialogueString: "Hence, repeated lateral movements lead to motion sickness,
      as our sense of proprioception detects minimal change in physical movements,
      yet our vision tells us that we are moving sideways. \r"
    m_ClearPreviousImage: 1
    m_MainImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 762a6196fad3d6d458bd5d806c203d8a, type: 3}
    m_VoiceoverClip: {fileID: 0}
  - m_DialogueString: "Now that you have experienced strafing, your next experience
      introduces another variant of movement for you to navigate through the level.\r"
    m_ClearPreviousImage: 1
    m_MainImage: {fileID: 0}
    m_VoiceoverClip: {fileID: 0}
  - m_DialogueString: "Whenever you are ready, head to the door on your left. \r"
    m_ClearPreviousImage: 1
    m_MainImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 6f13ccda2f65ea04c9ea4559772ef214, type: 3}
    m_VoiceoverClip: {fileID: 0}
